{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bea002c1-2545-4ffa-9b96-156e9dbb9d2a","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine, so I can't inspect it directly. But here's **how to determine the runtime and configure dumps**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Identify the Runtime\n\nRun these against your actual PID:\n\n```bash\n# If libcoreclr.so is loaded → CoreCLR; otherwise → NativeAOT\ngrep -q 'libcoreclr' /proc/<PID>/maps && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"NativeAOT\"\n```\n\nYou can also check if the binary is self-contained:\n```bash\nfile $(readlink /proc/<PID>/exe)\n# NativeAOT: statically linked, no dependency on libcoreclr\n# CoreCLR: dynamically linked, loads libcoreclr.so\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Configure Crash Dumps\n\n#### For CoreCLR (managed runtime):\n\n```bash\n# Set environment variables before launching the app:\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nThese are handled **by the CoreCLR runtime itself** — no OS-level config needed.\n\n#### For NativeAOT (or as a fallback):\n\nNativeAOT doesn't have built-in dump support — rely on the **OS kernel**:\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# Configure kernel core pattern (requires root)\necho '/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\n# Make persistent across reboots\necho 'kernel.core_pattern=/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.d/90-coredumps.conf\nsudo sysctl --system\n\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nIf your system uses **systemd-coredump** (check with `coredumpctl`), dumps are automatically collected under `/var/lib/systemd/coredump/` and you can retrieve them with:\n```bash\ncoredumpctl list          # list dumps\ncoredumpctl dump <PID>    # extract a dump\n```\n\n---\n\n### Quick Decision\n\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Mechanism** | `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` env vars | OS `core_pattern` / `systemd-coredump` |\n| **Dump analysis** | `dotnet-dump analyze` | `gdb` / `lldb` |\n| **Detection** | `libcoreclr.so` in `/proc/PID/maps` | No `libcoreclr.so` |\n\nRun the detection command on your live process and apply the matching configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3ceb4022-f4f7-48e1-97b2-d2a42e24aa0b","outputTokens":731,"requestId":"D7C5:246CF2:F70B6B:11D1B8E:69F2B670"},"id":"dee3c1a9-ce6b-4806-bec6-4aeef923b049","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:55:11.821Z","parentId":"3daa9508-7a4e-424b-8c59-425beb3a61f1"}
